# CODEOWNERS for containers/kubernetes-mcp-server
#
# Single source of truth for toolset ownership AND toolset labels.
# Order matters: the LAST matching pattern takes precedence.
#
# Each toolset block is introduced by a machine-readable marker on its own line:
#
#     # toolset: <name>
#
# The .github/workflows/toolset-triage.yaml workflow parses these markers to
# (a) apply/remove the `toolset/<name>` label on PRs based on their changed
# files, and (b) @-mention the block's owners. A marker tags every rule beneath
# it up to the next blank line.
#
# NOTE ON EXTERNAL CONTRIBUTORS:
# GitHub only auto-requests review from code owners that have *write* access to
# the repository. Most toolset owners below are external contributors who do not
# (and cannot) have write access, so GitHub will not auto-request them and will
# flag those lines with a "no write access" warning. They are listed here as the
# documented owners of their areas; the toolset-triage workflow @-mentions them
# on pull requests that touch their paths, which is what actually notifies them.

